-- Britain appoints HSBC, Linklaters as advisors for government sukuk bond
-- By Andy Bruce
-- Fri Jan 31, 2014 05:34AM EST
-- None



LONDON, Jan 31 (Reuters) - Britain's finance ministry said on Friday it has appointed HSBC <HSBA.L> and law firm Linklaters as advisors to assist in a planned issuance of a sukuk bond, part of the government's plan to build up London as a centre for Islamic finance .

"It is anticipated that issuance will take place during 2014-15 by way of a syndicated offering. The government anticipates recruiting additional syndicate members closer to the time," The Treasury said in a statement.